fishing zone in waters where the taiwanese government itself has 
banned driftnetting the ship allegedly cut its net and fled after 
being spotted by the cutter jarvis 
the jarvis shadowed the vessel for almost 700 miles before 
receiving permission from the taiwanese government to board 
wolfe said monday that a fish scale and fin found on the ship 
have been sent to a national marine fisheries service laboratory to 
see if they were from a salmon of north american origin 
