<TEXT>
scientists on monday aborted the launch 
of indias first mediumrange ballistic missile seconds before it 
was to lift off when computers detected an error in one of the 
rockets systems officials said 
one military official said a problem developed in the liquid 
fuel propellant of the 6 million missile and there would have been 
a big disaster had the countdown reached zero 
it was the second time in 11 days that scientists postponed the 
testfiring of the missile which experts say has the capability to 
carry a nuclear warhead 
the postponement was met by cheers and the blowing of conch 
shells by many of the 12000 villagers who were temporarily 
evacuated from their homes around the launch site in this eastern 
indian town overlooking the bay of bengal 
a government statement issued at the remote seaside missile 
center said the launch was called off when computers detected the 
data error 
it is not a major fault said vs arunachalam scientific 
adviser to the defense ministry and head of indias missile program 
at the launch site 
but a military official said scientists detected a leak in the 
missiles liquid fuel propellant 11 seconds before the scheduled 
firing 
had the scientists counted to zero it would have ended in a 
big disaster the official said speaking on condition of 
anonymity 
a previous attempt to fire the missile on april 20 was called 
off because of a snag in the ignition system 
military sources said the missile would likely be dismantled and 
every part checked before a third attempt is made 
scientists will postpone the launch for at least one week the 
sources said 
before the launch angry residents said prayers and held special 
ceremonies beseeching hindu gods and goddesses to prevent the 
missile from being fired the villagers fear they will be 
permanently shifted from their homes if the missile launch is 
successful and the test range is used for more firings 
the 7ton surfacetosurface missile has a range of 1550 
miles indian military experts say its first stage is boosted by a 
solid fuel propellant engine and its second stage is powered by a 
liquid fuel engine 
the range is sufficient to hit targets as far as iran in the 
west hong kong in the east china in the north and islands around 
the equator in the south western military officials said 
the missile named agni or fire in hindi can hit any 
target in neighboring pakistan indias longstanding adversary the 
two countries have fought three wars in the past 42 years 
defense experts said the oneton payload capability is more than 
enough for the missile to carry a nuclear warhead 
india has said its nuclear capacity will be used only for 
peaceful purposes but western military experts in new delhi said 
if india ever uses the missile in a war it might not carry a 
conventional warhead 
you need accuracy or a point target if you are using a 
conventional warhead said one western analyst speaking on 
condition of anonymity but if you are using a nuclear warhead 
the exact target does not matter 
india exploded a nuclear device 15 years ago and western 
experts estimate it would take indian scientists one week to 
assemble a nuclear device 
