project may be symbolic of an even greater and more lasting 
solidarity as america and the soviet union choose friendship over 
the folly of perpetual strife 
in a separate foreword soviet novelist daniil granin wrote that 
feeling the oneness of the earth and recognizing your own 
thoughts and feelings in other people is the best pathway to 
trust 
