<TEXT>
consumer products that release chemicals into 
the air which rip up the earths protective ozone layer would 
be regulated and those with nonessential uses would be phased out 
under legislation introduced monday by sen al gore dtenn 
gores bill is aimed at products ranging from leaking automobile 
air conditioners to noise horns to some types of fire extinguishers 
gore also introduced separate legislation to phase out within 
five years the most dangerous ozonedestroying chemicals and to 
impose a manufacturers tax on them 
an ozone layer conservation trust fund would be established to 
find alternatives to such chemicals as chloroflurocarbons and halon 
which have been shown to deplete the ozone layer of the 
stratosphere 
we know that these chemicals are ripping up the earths 
protective ozone layer and contributing to the greenhouse effect 
gore said in a statement 
we know that if we immediately stopped all use the problems 
theyve already created would linger on for decades he said 
hesitation simply cannot be tolerated we must move as quickly as 
possible to stop the destruction 
he said that simple common sense solutions are available 
now for application every day 
for example changing the way we service automobile air 
conditioners labeling and eventually stopping the production of 
nonessential consumer products such as noise horns or party 
streamers or certain cleaning fluids gore said 
he said us legislation can serve as a catalyst for efforts to 
eliminate the threat to the ozone layer by nations around the world 
my purpose is to sound an alarm loudly and clearly of 
imminent and grave danger and to describe a strategy for 
confronting this crisis with changes in our collective behavior and 
thinking which if made can forestall and prevent the horrendous 
prospect of an ecological collapse he said 
