<TEXT>
stock lists are forever offered from wall 
street one of the reasons being that wall street and its 
institutions and brokers have an increasingly shorter time horizon 
and an everchanging focus 
heres a list thats different its from main street prepared 
by serious amateurs who believe in fundamental analysis rather than 
hunches and longterm investing rather than shortterm trading 
the national association of investors corp has just released 
its top 100 stocks which it says is made up of the most widely 
held companies among individual investors and investment clubs 
around the country 
heading the list are walmart stores american family pepsico 
mcdonalds and american telephone amp telegraph four of which were 
also in the top five a year ago the newcomer mcdonalds jumped 
from 16th place 
advancing the furthest suggesting individual and club investors 
believe the shares have good longterm futures were rollins 
environmental from 80 to 34 upjohn from 92 to 51 and eastman 
kodak at 31 a newcomer to the list 
ken janke naic president observes that while the markets 
horizon seems to be getting shorter and its turnover greater and 
that many stocks seem to be chosen because of publicity the naics 
membership sticks to longterm goals 
fundamental to its investment concept is that company 
performance should be studied thoroughly before any commitment is 
made and that the investment should be made primarily in companies 
growing more rapidly than the economy 
in operating a portfolio it believes that regular investments 
even if in small amounts are necessary in order to offset the 
unpredictable ups and downs of the market and that dividends 
should be reinvested 
the effectiveness of that approach has been demonstrated in 
learned theses and simple comparisons but most effectively in the 
lives of club members who have paid tuitions bought homes taken 
trips and retired on their investments 
janke said a review of 1600 responses naic has 135000 
members identified at least two significant trends about 
individual investing habits 
first he said amateur and individual investors are taking 
their investing even more seriously than in the past placing more 
emphasis on facts and fundamentals rather than on hearsay or gossip 
a developing trend according to janke is the growing use of 
dividend reinvestment plans to help build club holdings and keep 
commission costs low more than onequarter of clubs appeared to be 
using such plans he said 
close to a thousand companies offer reinvestment plans in which 
dividends are transferred to the shareholders account with the 
company in addition most plans allow additional monthly or 
quarterly amounts to be sent directly to the company thereby 
eliminating or greatly reducing brokerage costs 
philip keating president of naics southeast florida council 
comments that the disciplined fundamentalist longterm 
perspective of members is often made difficult by the media and 
professional and institutional investors 
he claims the media and professional investors whom he 
described as the herd on the street and the flock on the 
block promote the notion of inout trading and distract from 
fundamental considerations 
wall street changes its opinion on stocks many times more 
often than the real longterm fundamentals of the underlying 
companies change he said in an analysis of the top 100 in 
better investing naics monthly magazine 
