pay a 2000 fine for releasing the documents to the abc television 
networks 2020 news show 
the judge last week ordered that the money be paid to the 
emergency trauma center at the milwaukee county medical complex 
biss formerly was an official with the national highway traffic 
safety administration and now is a private consultant he was hired 
as an expert by lawyers representing a man from monroe wis who 
is seeking unspecified damages from gm in a november 1985 car 
accident that left him a quadriplegic 
the accident victim david b mcguire says he was seated in the 
center of the back seat of a 1981 chevrolet chevette when the car 
collided headon with a pickup truck on wisconsin 69 in dane county 
mcguire says he was injured when he was thrust into the front of 
the car which was equipped with only two rear seat belts 
his lawsuit scheduled to go to trial oct 9 contends that if 
he had had a seat belt he would not have been injured 
biss admitted that he turned over to a producer for the abc news 
program last summer an internal document from gm that was under a 
protective court seal 
as an expert witness in the mcguire trial biss was allowed to 
view the document during the period in which lawyers gather 
information from the other side 
the document contained the results of a 1976 test by gm that it 
said showed that passengers strapped in rear lap belts undergo four 
times the force required to cause serious injury in headon 
collisions 
the 2020 program used the document in a july 1988 broadcast 
