it is the first test the court has heard under the newspaper 
preservation act it is likely it will decide the meaning of the 
act and the scope of the act for the future schultz said 
a federal appeals court panel in washington voted 21 in january 
to uphold the justice departments decision to allow the partial 
merger the full appeals court then split 54 in february in 
refusing to review the threejudge panels ruling 
the supreme court by a 72 vote cleared the way for the deal 
march 20 when it set aside an earlier postponement ordered by 
justice william j brennan 
only justices harry a blackmun and john paul stevens voted in 
march to continue the postponement the votes of four justices are 
needed to grant review to a formal appeal 
when the courts stay was lifted knightridder proposed 
proceeding with the partial merger gannett declined to do so 
no stay is in effect and the newspapers would have the option 
of merging while awaiting the supreme courts decision on the case 
gannett based in arlington va is the nations largest 
newspaper publishing group knightridder headquartered in miami 
is the second largest 
